<TITLE> Jalil skips court appearance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 17 (bdnews24.com)Ruling Awami League MP Abdul Jalil did not appear in court on Tuesday again because of illness in a tax evasion case. His counsel Arifur Rahman sought time for his appearance saying Jalil was in Singapore for treatment. Judge A N M Bashirullah of Dhaka Metropolitan Senior Special Judge's Court granted the request and set Jan 5 for the next hearing. The former AL general secretary also did not appear on Oct 26 on similar grounds . Deputy commissioner of National Board of Revenue Bazlur Rahman Khan filed the case on Oct 15 charging Jalil of evading Tk 4.07 lakh in income tax after hiding income worth Tk 54.60 lakh. The court on Oct 15 issued an arrest warrant against Jalilm whose controversial comments about his own party created a political storm in recent times. There was information of abnormal transaction in the bank accounts of Jalil and his wife at different times, which is not relevant with his income tax return statement, the case alleged. There were savings accounts and FDR in the name of their children, which were not mentioned in the statement. bd
